// Available widgets:

// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// | Widget name     | Description                                   | Type    | "extra" field          |
// |----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
// | WG_SSH_MARKER   | Indicate when on SSH connection               | static  | marker symbol          |
// | WG_SSH_ADDRESS  | Display server address when on SSH connection | static  | marker symbol          |
// | WG_USER_MARKER  | Display '#' for root, '$' for other users     | static  | 'bg' and 'fg' for root |
// | WG_USER_NAME    | Display user name (different color for root)  | static  | 'bg' and 'fg' for root |
// | WG_JOBS_NUMBER  | Display background jobs number if any         | runtime | -                      |
// | WG_ERROR_CODE   | Display return code for last command if error | runtime | -                      |
// | WG_GIT_BRANCH   | Display current git branch when in git repo   | runtime | marker symbol          |
// | WG_GIT_MARKER   | Indicate when in git repo                     | runtime | marker symbol          |
// | WG_CUSTOM       | Any custom text (e.g. bash promptescape-chars)| static  | content                |
// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

// Widget fields:
// fg - foreground color
// bg - background color
// term - symbol which separate current widget from the next
// fmt - additional formatting string, consisting from characters: 'b' (for bold), 'i' (for italic)
// extra - custom data, defined by widget type

// Colors: 
// Colors are represented as single 8-bit numbers, according to this table
// https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ANSI_escape_code#8-bit

